{Syntax:}\par polynomial_regression(Lst||Mtrx(A),[Lst],Intg(n))\par
\par Returns the coefficients (an,...a1,a0) of y=an*x^n+..a1x+a0): it is the best polynomial that approximates the points where the coordinates are the rows of A (or the 2 lists) (n is the 2nd argument).\par
{\par Example:}\par polynomial_regression([[1.0,1.0],[2.0,4.0],[3.0,9.0],[4.0,16.0]],3) returns [-0.0,1.0,-0.0,0.0]\par }